sub_title: Dutch Biology and Forest and Nature Conservation student from Wageningen University, specialised in Arctic ecology
summary:
I am a Dutch biology student at Wageningen University. During my studies I aimed at specializing in Arctic ecology. I have a deep love for the Arctic, apex predators, mammals, reptiles, and amphibians. During my studies I focused on Ecology, Inter Species Relationships, Genetics, Data Analysis and Ecological Modelling (statistics and mathematics). After my studies I would like to take a PhD position.

Coming year (2021) I will parttake in an expedition in the Yukon, Canada, as a trainnee expedition leader for a research expedition. With this I hope to further develop my skills regarding: field work and research experience, leadership qualities and outdoor experience. With the aim to create my own research expeditions during my future professional carreer in research.
